title: After Near Wipeout in Election, Israeli Left Wonders: What Now?
description: Support for Israel’s left collapsed against Benjamin Netanyahu and his far-right alliance in last week’s election. To regain relevance, the left’s leaders say they need to change — but disagree on how.
dc:creator: Patrick Kingsley
media:credit: Avishag Shaar-Yashuv for The New York Times
media:description: Empty ballot boxes in Kibbutz Holda. Israel’s Jewish-led left-leaning parties, long the standard-bearers for negotiations with the Palestinians, suffered a near wipeout in the recent election.
